Package: duckbotos-meta
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 duckbotos-base,
 duckbotos-hermes,
 duckbotos-openclaw,
 duckbotos-lm-studio,
 duckbotos-browseros,
 duckbotos-computer-use
Description: DuckBotOS — Agent-first Linux with Hermes + OpenClaw
 DuckBotOS is an Ubuntu-based Linux distribution where AI agents are
 the primary desktop interface. Boot into Hermes, OpenClaw, or a
 hybrid workstation mode.
 .
 This meta-package installs the complete DuckBotOS experience:
  - Hermes agent OS as the primary shell/UI
  - OpenClaw as a verified/secondary agent
  - LM Studio as a first-class local model provider
  - BrowserOS as the default agentic web browser
  - computer-use-linux for desktop automation
  - Weston kiosk for agent dashboard display
 .
 Supports NVIDIA, AMD, and CPU-only hardware targets.
 Requires Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (Noble Numbat).

Package: duckbotos-base
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 ubuntu-desktop-minimal,
 weston,
 xdg-desktop-portal,
 xdg-utils,
 curl,
 wget,
 git,
 htop,
 tmux,
 fish,
 openssh-client,
 ufw,
 unattended-upgrades,
 apparmor,
 apparmor-utils,
 firejail
Description: DuckBotOS base system — Weston kiosk + shell utilities
 Minimal base for DuckBotOS. Installs Weston compositor (kiosk mode),
 agent-facing shell utilities, and security tooling (AppArmor, firejail).
 .
 Installs no AI/agent packages — those are in mode-specific packages.

Package: duckbotos-hermes
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 duckbotos-base,
 hermesos-agent
Description: DuckBotOS Hermes agent mode
 Installs Hermes as the primary desktop agent for DuckBotOS.
 Hermes boots as a fullscreen shell replacing the traditional desktop.
 .
 Includes:
  - hermesos-agent (primary agent daemon)
  - hermes-nlpkg (natural language package manager)
  - hermesos-watchdog (predictive resource orchestrator)
  - OpenAI-compatible REST API on port 8000
  - Hermes tools exposed via D-Bus and Unix socket IPC
 .
 This is the primary "AI-first" experience.

Package: duckbotos-openclaw
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 duckbotos-base,
 openclaw-agent
Description: DuckBotOS OpenClaw agent mode
 Installs OpenClaw as the primary desktop agent for DuckBotOS.
 OpenClaw boots as a fullscreen agent interface.
 .
 Includes:
  - openclaw-agent (agent daemon, port 18797)
  - openclaw-gateway (MCP bridge, port 3850)
  - ACP protocol server (port 18794)
  - WebSocket streaming (port 18796)
  - Sub-conscious memory daemon (port 4001)
  - Agent mesh networking (port 4000)
 .
 Use for OpenClaw-native workflows.

Package: duckbotos-lm-studio
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 duckbotos-base,
 lm-studio-server
Description: DuckBotOS LM Studio — local model provider
 Installs LM Studio as a first-class local model provider for DuckBotOS.
 .
 Includes:
  - llmster daemon (headless model server)
  - lms CLI (model management, port 1234)
  - OpenAI-compatible REST API (/v1 endpoints)
  - JIT model loading (auto-loads on first inference request)
  - GPU-accelerated inference (CUDA/ROCm when available)
  - Systemd service: lmstudio.service
 .
 Models are managed from the OS UI or via `lms` CLI.
 Default model install path: ~/.lmstudio/models/

Package: duckbotos-browseros
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 duckbotos-base,
 browseros
Description: DuckBotOS BrowserOS — default agentic web browser
 Installs BrowserOS as the default agentic web browser for DuckBotOS.
 .
 Includes:
  - BrowserOS Chromium fork (agent-capable browser)
  - browseros-cli (Bun MCP server, port 9003)
  - 53+ browser automation tools via MCP protocol
  - Agent mode (Claude Opus 4.5, or any OpenAI-compatible model)
  - Chat mode (any model including LM Studio local models)
 .
 Set as default browser via update-alternatives.
 Registered as x-www-browser for OS-wide use.
 Note: browseros-cli `status` command is known to report
 "disconnected" even when working — use `health` and `pages` instead.

Package: duckbotos-computer-use
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 duckbotos-base,
 computer-use-linux
Description: DuckBotOS computer-use — desktop automation MCP server
 Installs computer-use-linux as a systemd-per-user MCP server for
 automated desktop interaction and accessibility-driven control.
 .
 Includes:
  - AT-SPI2 accessibility bus integration
  - Wayland portal for screen capture and input
  - MCP protocol server for OpenClaw/Hermes tool calling
  - Per-user systemd service: computer-use@username.service
  - Configurable via ~/.config/computer-use-linux.yaml
 .
 Requires Wayland session (Weston kiosk in DuckBotOS).
 Not compatible with X11-only sessions.
